SubmitterDescription.SubmitterName: International Standards For Cytogenomic Arrays Consortium (ISCA)

SampleDescription.Description: A limited chromosome study confirmed that this individual has two genetically unique cell lines: one triploid (69,XXY) and one diploid (46,XY). FISH studies confirmed the presence of triploidy in 90.0% of metaphase cells and 84.0% of interphase nuclei from a PHA-stimulated culture.
